1
00:00:07,675 --> 00:00:11,579
When I heard that Chief Sangenya
married Manager Yashiro

2
00:00:11,746 --> 00:00:13,280
at that scenic seaside town,

3
00:00:13,514 --> 00:00:15,516
I congratulated them
from the bottom of the heart.

4
00:00:16,384 --> 00:00:18,819
Then I graduated

5
00:00:18,986 --> 00:00:22,490
from Chief Sangenya
and became an independent adult.

6
00:00:23,257 --> 00:00:27,228
However, ever since that guy appeared,

7
00:00:27,728 --> 00:00:29,897
I realized something.

8
00:00:30,831 --> 00:00:34,301
Chief Sangenya and Mr. Rusudo
are against each other at times

9
00:00:34,468 --> 00:00:36,303
and collaborate at other times.

10
00:00:36,470 --> 00:00:40,307
That's because they are equal
as realtors and as human beings.

11
00:00:41,809 --> 00:00:45,446
But I'm… I'm not equal.

12
00:00:45,613 --> 00:00:48,315
Mr. Rusudo is an equal, but I'm…

13
00:00:52,119 --> 00:00:54,121
-Niwano!
-Yes!

14
00:00:54,455 --> 00:00:56,056
Do you have a stomachache?

15
00:00:56,223 --> 00:00:57,358
Not at all.

16
00:00:57,525 --> 00:00:59,927
Then don't make that strange noise!

17
00:01:00,294 --> 00:01:01,829
I'm sorry.

18
00:01:01,996 --> 00:01:05,666
See? I'm not treated as an equal.

19
00:01:06,434 --> 00:01:07,468
Niwano!

20
00:01:07,635 --> 00:01:08,569
Yes!

21
00:01:11,672 --> 00:01:12,773
Ouch.

22
00:01:15,543 --> 00:01:18,913
What a peaceful afternoon.
It's like when I was a manager.

23
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:22,049
Niwano is with Sanchi again today.

24
00:01:22,216 --> 00:01:25,586
Of course. Niwano is one
of the Sangenya Children.

25
00:01:25,753 --> 00:01:27,855
Child? He's just a slave.

26
00:01:28,022 --> 00:01:30,157
-You shouldn't say that.
-Agreed.

27
00:01:30,324 --> 00:01:33,093
I'm going to the bathroom.

28
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,595
Don't run away, Niwano.

29
00:01:35,329 --> 00:01:37,331
It's not bad to listen
to those kinds of opinions.

30
00:01:39,667 --> 00:01:45,172
Ever since Rusudo appeared,
Niwano does seem like a servant now.

31
00:01:45,639 --> 00:01:47,308
Demoted!

32
00:01:47,475 --> 00:01:48,742
That's harsh!

33
00:01:48,909 --> 00:01:52,379
Shirasu used to say
that he was Sanchi's dog!

34
00:01:52,546 --> 00:01:53,414
What are you doing?

35
00:01:54,882 --> 00:01:55,950
Nothing.

36
00:02:00,387 --> 00:02:01,322
I'm back.

37
00:02:01,755 --> 00:02:03,324
Welcome back!

38
00:02:03,724 --> 00:02:05,926
You all seem energetic.

39
00:02:06,093 --> 00:02:08,062
It's good that you are motivated.

40
00:02:08,229 --> 00:02:14,034
Niwano, Ms. Munakata,
your 16:00 appointment is coming at 15:00.

41
00:02:14,201 --> 00:02:16,737
What? It's already 15:00.
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

42
00:02:17,071 --> 00:02:18,606
You just came back!

43
00:02:18,772 --> 00:02:20,407
I'll go meet my client.

44
00:02:21,008 --> 00:02:22,643
See you later!

45
00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:26,447
Manager, the property in
Yotsuya sold for ¥40 million.

46
00:02:26,614 --> 00:02:28,315
Oh, good work.

47
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:31,652
It is my job to sell properties.

48
00:02:32,086 --> 00:02:33,053
Exactly.

49
00:02:33,954 --> 00:02:37,758
Mr. Fuse, Mr. Hachinohe, Mr. Takuma and
Kagimura, who are nice and relaxed.

50
00:02:37,925 --> 00:02:40,027
What is your job?

51
00:02:42,997 --> 00:02:45,466
-Go post flyers. Go!
-Yes!

52
00:02:50,471 --> 00:02:53,407
I'm Niwano. Nice to meet you.

53
00:02:53,874 --> 00:02:58,412
-So…
-I would like to sell my house.

54
00:02:58,579 --> 00:02:59,980
Will you be looking for a new house?

55
00:03:00,147 --> 00:03:02,850
No, I want to sell my house…

56
00:03:03,484 --> 00:03:06,053
and devote myself to my last dream.

57
00:03:06,353 --> 00:03:07,388
Oh…

58
00:03:07,555 --> 00:03:11,725
Um, I'm actually against selling
the house.

59
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:13,294
What?

60
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:17,498
Sumire, you said it was okay
for me to sell last night.

61
00:03:17,665 --> 00:03:22,369
But if you really think about it,
that house is our only asset.

62
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:27,308
If my dream comes true,
you won't have to worry at all.

63
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:30,644
So there's a cafe by the station for sale.

64
00:03:30,811 --> 00:03:33,681
I want to run
a cake specialty store there.

65
00:03:33,847 --> 00:03:38,819
I'll sell cakes and run cake-making
classes. Isn't it wonderful!

66
00:03:39,887 --> 00:03:43,958
But you've had galleries
and a health food restaurant.

67
00:03:44,124 --> 00:03:46,760
She sold the second home Dad bequeathed,

68
00:03:46,927 --> 00:03:48,162
and her savings are gone!

69
00:03:48,329 --> 00:03:49,530
It'll be fine this time.

70
00:03:50,297 --> 00:03:53,701
So who's name is the house in right now?

71
00:03:53,867 --> 00:03:55,736
It's in my mother's and my name.

72
00:03:58,172 --> 00:04:04,712
So unless your daughter agrees,
it will be difficult to sell your house.

73
00:04:07,348 --> 00:04:10,384
She said it was fine to sell last night.

74
00:04:10,551 --> 00:04:13,954
That's terrible of you
to change your mind now.

75
00:04:14,121 --> 00:04:16,123
What about my dream?

76
00:04:16,290 --> 00:04:18,459
It might be the last dream of my life.

77
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:22,696
I'm hesitating because
I'm thinking of our future.

78
00:04:23,497 --> 00:04:24,765
Mrs. Munakata.

79
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:28,535
I will sell that house.

80
00:04:29,003 --> 00:04:30,037
Who is she?

81
00:04:30,204 --> 00:04:32,539
-She is…
-I am a realtor!

82
00:04:32,706 --> 00:04:36,810
There is no house I cannot sell!

83
00:04:52,026 --> 00:04:53,127
WEST SHINJUKU SPORTS CENTER

84
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:54,695
CHEVALIER FENCING CLUB

85
00:04:57,297 --> 00:05:00,134
Satoshi, that's a nice scarf.

86
00:05:11,345 --> 00:05:12,212
What's the matter?

87
00:05:13,013 --> 00:05:14,081
I locked the door.

88
00:05:14,248 --> 00:05:15,149
Why?

89
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:17,851
So that the security guard won't
interrupt us like the last time.

90
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:20,954
Did the security guard interrupt us?

91
00:05:21,121 --> 00:05:22,222
Kenji!

92
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:25,693
I like you.

93
00:05:27,061 --> 00:05:29,329
I like you too, Satoshi.

94
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:32,299
-That's not how I mean it.
-Then how?

95
00:05:33,033 --> 00:05:35,903
I love you!

96
00:05:42,543 --> 00:05:43,644
I see.

97
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:49,116
Kenji, you're nice, capable,
and beautiful.

98
00:05:49,283 --> 00:05:51,051
I love you so much

99
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:54,021
it's a struggle to keep it to myself.

100
00:06:00,894 --> 00:06:07,000
Thank you, but I love Ms. Sangenya.

101
00:06:08,936 --> 00:06:13,073
Ms. Sangenya may not be kind

102
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:16,310
but she's capable and beautiful.

103
00:06:17,311 --> 00:06:21,014
I struggle every day to keep

104
00:06:23,016 --> 00:06:24,384
my love for her to myself.

105
00:06:24,852 --> 00:06:28,555
Then do you plan to take Ms. Sangenya
away from Manager?

106
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:30,958
-I'm not thinking that!
-Then what do you want to do?

107
00:06:35,863 --> 00:06:37,164
I wonder…

108
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:42,169
What would you do, Satoshi?

109
00:06:44,037 --> 00:06:44,972
Me?

110
00:06:48,375 --> 00:06:49,243
With you?

111
00:06:54,615 --> 00:06:56,750
Maybe a kiss?

112
00:06:57,718 --> 00:06:58,552
A kiss?

113
00:06:59,386 --> 00:07:00,287
A kiss.

114
00:07:01,188 --> 00:07:02,055
Kiss.

115
00:07:04,191 --> 00:07:05,092
Kiss Kenji?

116
00:07:05,726 --> 00:07:07,294
Kiss Ms. Sangenya?

117
00:07:10,464 --> 00:07:11,365
Even if I did…

118
00:07:11,532 --> 00:07:12,566
Even if you did…

119
00:07:12,733 --> 00:07:14,835
-Then…
-Then…

120
00:07:17,004 --> 00:07:19,139
No, no, no.

121
00:07:21,909 --> 00:07:23,544
What do I want to do?

122
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:26,647
I wonder what I want to do?

123
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:36,890
Is someone here?
This place is closing now.

124
00:07:37,057 --> 00:07:37,991
Okay!

125
00:07:42,996 --> 00:07:43,897
Let's go home.

126
00:07:50,304 --> 00:07:51,138
Kenji.

127
00:07:52,673 --> 00:07:53,507
What?

128
00:07:55,008 --> 00:07:55,876
Your shoes.

129
00:08:00,514 --> 00:08:01,415
Thank you.

130
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:13,126
What's that sigh for?

131
00:08:13,293 --> 00:08:16,029
I thought I had graduated.

132
00:08:16,463 --> 00:08:18,966
What? You didn't graduate from school?

133
00:08:19,132 --> 00:08:21,702
No, I did graduate from school…

134
00:08:22,436 --> 00:08:24,972
Oh, is it about Sanchi?

135
00:08:25,138 --> 00:08:27,007
How can you tell?

136
00:08:27,808 --> 00:08:28,842
Welcome.

137
00:08:31,278 --> 00:08:32,980
Oh, you are here.

138
00:08:33,146 --> 00:08:34,514
-Whisky and water.
-Sure.

139
00:08:34,681 --> 00:08:36,583
Was it better if I wasn't here?

140
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:37,718
I don't care.

141
00:08:38,352 --> 00:08:39,887
What's wrong, Prince Adachi?

142
00:08:40,354 --> 00:08:41,622
Nothing.

143
00:08:42,189 --> 00:08:43,357
Could you listen to me too?

144
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:49,096
I want to graduate
from Chief Sangenya… or maybe not.

145
00:08:49,263 --> 00:08:51,899
But if I don't graduate,

146
00:08:52,065 --> 00:08:54,434
I can't move forward…

147
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,138
Mr. Adachi? Mr. Adachi!

148
00:08:58,472 --> 00:08:59,673
Are you listening to me?

149
00:09:00,073 --> 00:09:01,041
I am.

150
00:09:01,642 --> 00:09:05,112
-"Graduate" is a nice word.
-What?

151
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:07,614
Prince Adachi, do you have someone
you want to graduate from?

152
00:09:09,116 --> 00:09:13,287
I was asked what I wanted to do,
but I couldn't answer it.

153
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:17,391
I don't know what I was looking for.

154
00:09:18,158 --> 00:09:21,194
You'll find an answer one day.
You will graduate.

155
00:09:21,795 --> 00:09:23,096
Graduate.

156
00:09:23,263 --> 00:09:26,266
Now, I'll chant a spell,
so you can graduate.

157
00:09:27,701 --> 00:09:31,038
Chichin pui-pui, graduate,
graduate, graduate!

158
00:09:34,007 --> 00:09:34,841
How is it?

159
00:09:35,609 --> 00:09:36,476
Thank you.

160
00:09:37,644 --> 00:09:39,212
I'll graduate from Chief Sangenya too.

161
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:40,714
Here's your drink.

162
00:09:40,881 --> 00:09:44,818
I think I'm not a real man unless
I graduate from Chief Sangenya.

163
00:09:44,985 --> 00:09:47,087
I think it's fine
even if you are not a real man.

164
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:48,555
What do you mean?

165
00:09:48,722 --> 00:09:49,890
Do your best, Niwano.

166
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:53,460
Do your best and graduate.

167
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:56,697
Yes.

168
00:09:57,097 --> 00:09:58,865
Let's have a graduation party.

169
00:09:59,299 --> 00:10:01,301
-Yeah!
-Let's drink!

170
00:10:01,468 --> 00:10:02,936
Yeah!

171
00:10:05,639 --> 00:10:11,244
Six months until graduation

172
00:10:11,878 --> 00:10:17,617
They say you'll find an answer

173
00:10:17,784 --> 00:10:23,657
During your youth

174
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:30,597
All you do is hesitate

175
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:33,600
Oh.

176
00:10:36,203 --> 00:10:38,538
Hello, are you on your way home?

177
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:39,573
Yes.

178
00:10:40,707 --> 00:10:42,042
It's cold again today.

179
00:10:42,542 --> 00:10:43,744
Yes.

180
00:10:45,379 --> 00:10:47,414
Do you want to go get oden?

181
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:49,816
I want to warm up.

182
00:10:50,317 --> 00:10:56,356
Right, but dinner is prepared
for me at home.

183
00:10:59,793 --> 00:11:05,599
It's prepared, but your wife
won't be home until late at night?

184
00:11:05,766 --> 00:11:07,567
You know well.

185
00:11:07,901 --> 00:11:10,837
We talked about it the other day.

186
00:11:12,873 --> 00:11:16,309
There's an oden shop run
by my friend down the street.

187
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:29,990
This oden shop is quite far.

188
00:11:32,025 --> 00:11:34,394
The oden shop is not where I want to go.

189
00:11:39,499 --> 00:11:40,367
I want to go here.

190
00:11:41,735 --> 00:11:43,036
PERSEUS
VACANT

191
00:11:43,203 --> 00:11:44,137
Please.

192
00:11:46,773 --> 00:11:48,175
I'm fine even if it's just for fun.

193
00:11:48,742 --> 00:11:52,646
No, I can't do something like this
with you just for fun.

194
00:11:52,813 --> 00:11:53,780
Just once.

195
00:11:55,749 --> 00:11:57,784
I won't ask for more.

196
00:12:00,387 --> 00:12:06,293
Just this once, just this once,
let's comfort each other.

197
00:12:08,829 --> 00:12:10,430
We are adults.

198
00:12:11,731 --> 00:12:13,967
Don't you think that's allowed?

199
00:12:16,503 --> 00:12:20,874
Mr. Yashiro, why did you come here?

200
00:12:21,041 --> 00:12:23,310
Well, you said we're going
to this oden shop--

201
00:12:23,477 --> 00:12:24,478
No!

202
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:28,048
You feel the same way as I do.

203
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,718
Someone is looking.

204
00:12:31,885 --> 00:12:33,086
No! No!

205
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:35,222
-Mr. Yashiro! Please!
-No!

206
00:12:35,388 --> 00:12:37,757
-Let's not! No!
-Let's go.

207
00:12:38,625 --> 00:12:39,860
It's full.

208
00:12:40,026 --> 00:12:42,329
-Let's go next door then!
-What?

209
00:12:42,496 --> 00:12:44,531
No! Next door is not good!

210
00:12:44,698 --> 00:12:46,366
Um…

211
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:48,168
Why did you come all the way
over here then?

212
00:12:48,335 --> 00:12:50,871
I can't betray my wife.

213
00:12:51,037 --> 00:12:53,373
I love my wife.

214
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:55,275
You are the worst!

215
00:12:56,243 --> 00:12:58,411
I'm sorry! I'm really sorry!

216
00:12:59,146 --> 00:13:01,181
I wish you luck at the store!

217
00:13:05,485 --> 00:13:06,853
Chicken.

218
00:13:12,692 --> 00:13:14,628
What am I doing?

219
00:13:25,105 --> 00:13:27,908
Hello everybody. Rock 'n' roll!

220
00:13:28,074 --> 00:13:30,043
Hey, is Niwano here? Niwano?

221
00:13:30,210 --> 00:13:32,212
-Niwano is out…
-Ah!

222
00:13:32,379 --> 00:13:35,348
Are you Hachio Hachinohe
who's fluent in Chinese?

223
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:38,318
You sold room 808.

224
00:13:38,485 --> 00:13:40,453
-Nihao.
-Nihao.

225
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:42,155
May I ask for your name?

226
00:13:42,322 --> 00:13:45,659
Ah, your articulation is bad.
What's your name?

227
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:50,230
You married and divorced
that unmotivated female worker.

228
00:13:50,597 --> 00:13:54,000
Ah! You are the Prince
who's loved by the madams.

229
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:58,004
You are the manager
who's bossed around by a strong wife.

230
00:13:59,539 --> 00:14:03,476
You are the exquisitely beautiful,
Queen of realtors.

231
00:14:03,643 --> 00:14:05,278
Your favorite line is "Go!"

232
00:14:05,445 --> 00:14:07,781
Ms. Chief Sangenya.

233
00:14:08,982 --> 00:14:12,552
Um, I don't mean to be rude,
but who are you?

234
00:14:12,719 --> 00:14:14,354
Are you Niwano's client?

235
00:14:14,521 --> 00:14:16,323
Me? Niwano.

236
00:14:17,824 --> 00:14:19,192
Dad!

237
00:14:21,995 --> 00:14:24,130
What are you doing here?

238
00:14:25,098 --> 00:14:27,334
I'm sorry, let me introduce myself.

239
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:30,704
I am Niwano's father.

240
00:14:31,171 --> 00:14:33,540
It's Shigeo as in Shigeo Nagashima.

241
00:14:33,707 --> 00:14:35,609
My name is Shigeo Niwano.

242
00:14:35,775 --> 00:14:37,277
What are you doing here?

243
00:14:37,911 --> 00:14:40,747
This is Unagi Pie from Hamamatsu.

244
00:14:40,914 --> 00:14:42,682
Thank you very much.

245
00:14:43,083 --> 00:14:46,152
I'm thinking of selling my house
in Hamamatsu.

246
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:51,858
I figured I would ask my realtor son
to do it, so I came to Tokyo.

247
00:14:52,392 --> 00:14:53,560
Let's do this.

248
00:14:54,127 --> 00:14:55,295
Let's do this.

249
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:59,065
I don't want you to come so suddenly.

250
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:02,602
Even if I told you ahead of time,
you won't welcome me anyway.

251
00:15:02,769 --> 00:15:04,170
That's true.

252
00:15:04,337 --> 00:15:08,341
I have a great idea again.

253
00:15:08,508 --> 00:15:10,844
It'll be successful for sure this time!
Join me!

254
00:15:11,011 --> 00:15:12,145
I won't sell the house.

255
00:15:12,312 --> 00:15:17,183
Don't say that. I used up my savings
for that live music club.

256
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:18,885
The only thing worth anything
is the house.

257
00:15:20,787 --> 00:15:24,157
So with the last music club, I thought
to change Japan's music industry

258
00:15:24,324 --> 00:15:26,092
with the rock n' roll lifestyle

259
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:30,664
that I built in Hamamatsu.
I obviously didn't know my place

260
00:15:30,830 --> 00:15:34,467
and failed miserably,
but it's okay this time.

261
00:15:35,568 --> 00:15:40,840
This time, I'm starting a takoyaki
business. It's a practical business.

262
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:45,078
You only need about seven square meters
for a takoyaki shop.

263
00:15:45,245 --> 00:15:46,646
It'll be a success!

264
00:15:46,813 --> 00:15:48,915
It's the last challenge of my life!

265
00:15:51,251 --> 00:15:52,285
What's with your attitude?

266
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:57,791
You know, you'll be homeless
if you lose that house.

267
00:15:57,957 --> 00:16:04,197
I'm saying that when I become successful,
I won't go homeless.

268
00:16:05,865 --> 00:16:08,301
I see. Then fine.

269
00:16:08,902 --> 00:16:13,707
I'll just ask the genius realtor,
Chief Sangenya.

270
00:16:14,841 --> 00:16:15,675
You shocked me.

271
00:16:15,842 --> 00:16:17,677
-Mr. Shigeo Niwano.
-Yes!

272
00:16:17,844 --> 00:16:19,813
I will sell that house.

273
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:20,847
Really?

274
00:16:21,381 --> 00:16:24,818
You sure are a genius realtor.

275
00:16:25,318 --> 00:16:26,586
You're so helpful!

276
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,723
My job is to sell properties!

277
00:16:30,557 --> 00:16:33,426
I wanted to hear that.

278
00:16:33,593 --> 00:16:35,395
Chief Sangenya, that home in Hamamatsu

279
00:16:35,562 --> 00:16:38,031
was inherited from my mother,
and it's in my name as well.

280
00:16:38,198 --> 00:16:40,934
I won't sell the home left to me
by my mother.

281
00:16:41,101 --> 00:16:43,269
There is no property I can't sell.

282
00:16:43,436 --> 00:16:44,437
She said it again.

283
00:16:44,604 --> 00:16:47,640
I know, but could you not say
that line this time?

284
00:16:47,807 --> 00:16:49,709
I leave everything to you.

285
00:16:49,876 --> 00:16:50,977
I won't sell.

286
00:16:51,144 --> 00:16:53,747
There is no property I can't sell.

287
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:06,092
Hey, what's the matter? Are you okay?

288
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:08,661
Manager, could you do something about it?

289
00:17:08,828 --> 00:17:10,797
What do you want me to do?

290
00:17:10,964 --> 00:17:14,300
Chief Sangenya told my father
that she will sell my house in Hamamatsu,

291
00:17:14,467 --> 00:17:15,635
but it's also in my name.

292
00:17:15,802 --> 00:17:19,372
I don't want to sell. Please do
something and stop Chief Sangenya.

293
00:17:19,539 --> 00:17:23,977
If it is also in your name,
then your father can't do anything.

294
00:17:24,144 --> 00:17:27,046
That's right, Niwano. So calm down.

295
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:32,185
But when Chief Sangenya says she'll sell,
who knows what she'll do.

296
00:17:32,352 --> 00:17:34,654
I will sell that house.

297
00:17:34,821 --> 00:17:38,491
There is no property I can't sell.
She said that!

298
00:17:38,658 --> 00:17:40,994
That's a problem.

299
00:17:41,528 --> 00:17:43,129
Niwano, give it up.

300
00:17:43,296 --> 00:17:45,498
What are you saying, Mr. Hachinohe?

301
00:17:45,665 --> 00:17:49,436
Calm down. I'm sure Sangenya has an idea.

302
00:17:49,602 --> 00:17:50,837
She is aggressive

303
00:17:51,004 --> 00:17:53,706
but won't do anything
unprofitable for the clients.

304
00:17:56,609 --> 00:17:58,711
Am I considered her client now?

305
00:17:58,878 --> 00:18:02,015
Niwano, Ms. Munakata is on line one.

306
00:18:02,549 --> 00:18:03,416
Okay.

307
00:18:04,818 --> 00:18:07,787
Everyone, please help me out.

308
00:18:08,221 --> 00:18:09,823
Thank you very much.

309
00:18:09,989 --> 00:18:13,793
You should come visit Hamamatsu
sometime soon. The fish are good.

310
00:18:14,093 --> 00:18:18,031
It's not just eels.
The bonito and tuna are tasty too.

311
00:18:18,198 --> 00:18:19,299
Is that so?

312
00:18:19,466 --> 00:18:25,538
Oh, but I like takoyaki too.
Life is a dream. See you!

313
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:31,845
My mother started to spend a lot
once she married my father.

314
00:18:32,011 --> 00:18:35,381
So my father almost divorced her,

315
00:18:35,548 --> 00:18:39,285
but decided not to
since she was pregnant with me.

316
00:18:39,686 --> 00:18:46,226
All she does is dream and spends
everything she can get her hands on.

317
00:18:47,227 --> 00:18:49,095
That sounds familiar.

318
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:55,168
No, I understand your pain.

319
00:18:55,935 --> 00:18:58,104
After all,
your mom is your only family left.

320
00:18:58,271 --> 00:19:02,475
Right. She's my mom,
so I can't push her away.

321
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:07,614
I'm glad I was able to talk to you though.

322
00:19:08,448 --> 00:19:13,386
No matter what Ms. Sangenya says,
please protect my house.

323
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:14,988
Yes.

324
00:19:15,355 --> 00:19:18,458
In my type of work,
not selling is not an option.

325
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:21,961
But in this case, I think
it's better if you don't sell.

326
00:19:22,128 --> 00:19:23,496
Let's try our best, Ms. Munakata.

327
00:19:24,197 --> 00:19:25,131
Yes.

328
00:19:26,132 --> 00:19:28,268
-Good work.
-Good work.

329
00:19:29,002 --> 00:19:31,070
I'm sorry about my dad today.

330
00:19:31,371 --> 00:19:35,074
Well, you're having to deal
with a lot of problems too, huh Niwano?

331
00:19:35,241 --> 00:19:36,609
He embarrasses me.

332
00:19:36,776 --> 00:19:38,044
Don't say that.

333
00:19:38,211 --> 00:19:39,846
I really am embarrassed by him.

334
00:19:42,549 --> 00:19:48,555
My dad was never really home
when I was a child.

335
00:19:48,721 --> 00:19:52,158
I think he was going around
different women's houses.

336
00:19:52,325 --> 00:19:54,994
I think my mother passed away young
because of that stress.

337
00:19:55,662 --> 00:19:59,332
You've become a serious person
to not be like your father.

338
00:19:59,499 --> 00:20:01,868
I've lived my life wanting
to reject his DNA.

339
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:05,872
So that house you were talking about
was your mother's home?

340
00:20:06,039 --> 00:20:10,610
So that dad of yours is trying
to use up your mother's property?

341
00:20:10,777 --> 00:20:12,712
Yes, he's the worst father ever.

342
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:15,782
Niwano, you are quite close
to your dad though.

343
00:20:16,616 --> 00:20:17,984
We are not close.

344
00:20:18,151 --> 00:20:20,019
You talk to him a lot about work, right?

345
00:20:20,186 --> 00:20:24,724
He knew about Mr. Takuma's articulation
and how Mr. Hachinohe sold room 808.

346
00:20:24,891 --> 00:20:28,494
Oh, I guess you told him
that I am controlled by my wife!

347
00:20:28,661 --> 00:20:35,301
No! I send him money every month.
He calls me to thank me.

348
00:20:35,468 --> 00:20:38,304
Then he'd ask me how work is going,
so I end up telling him.

349
00:20:38,705 --> 00:20:40,106
You send him money?

350
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,275
You are such a good person, Niwano.

351
00:20:42,942 --> 00:20:44,711
I want to cut ties with him,

352
00:20:44,877 --> 00:20:47,714
but when I think that he's my only dad
I chicken out…

353
00:20:48,448 --> 00:20:49,649
I'm indecisive.

354
00:20:49,816 --> 00:20:51,050
You are just kind.

355
00:20:51,451 --> 00:20:53,519
I can't deal with it.

356
00:20:54,287 --> 00:20:57,957
But I think if I do
as Chief Sangenya says this time,

357
00:20:58,124 --> 00:21:00,660
I'll be nothing more than Sanchi's dog
for the rest of my life.

358
00:21:00,827 --> 00:21:03,663
This time, I can't lose
against Chief Sangenya!

359
00:21:04,197 --> 00:21:06,132
You are trying to change, Niwano.

360
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:09,602
I'll win against Chief Sangenya,
and I'll graduate too!

361
00:21:10,436 --> 00:21:11,604
Graduate?

362
00:21:24,584 --> 00:21:26,019
I went and saw the property.

363
00:21:30,423 --> 00:21:31,491
A souvenir from Hamamatsu.

364
00:21:34,027 --> 00:21:34,994
It's Unagi Pie.

365
00:21:36,596 --> 00:21:38,364
I hear it's a night-time snack.

366
00:21:43,336 --> 00:21:44,337
Thank you.

367
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:48,775
Oh, it's just a souvenir.

368
00:21:48,941 --> 00:21:51,711
No, I'm not talking about the souvenir.

369
00:21:53,713 --> 00:21:54,547
Thank you.

370
00:21:57,417 --> 00:21:58,618
What's the matter?

371
00:21:59,986 --> 00:22:00,820
Nothing.

372
00:22:01,454 --> 00:22:03,856
I will repay you for this.

373
00:22:08,361 --> 00:22:12,765
Could you repay me now?

374
00:22:16,002 --> 00:22:20,239
OKLAHOMA MIXER

375
00:22:55,675 --> 00:22:56,609
Thank you very much.

376
00:22:56,776 --> 00:22:57,677
Not at all.

377
00:22:59,045 --> 00:23:02,882
I was thinking about what I wanted
to do with you.

378
00:23:03,049 --> 00:23:04,050
This was it?

379
00:23:04,584 --> 00:23:08,855
Yes, I didn't get to dance with Manchichi

380
00:23:09,021 --> 00:23:14,460
on sports day in sixth grade. That was
bothering me. I feel great now.

381
00:23:14,994 --> 00:23:15,928
I see.

382
00:23:17,029 --> 00:23:17,864
See you.

383
00:23:19,565 --> 00:23:20,900
The exit is that way.

384
00:23:23,236 --> 00:23:24,303
Thank you.

385
00:23:25,138 --> 00:23:27,039
OPEN HOUSE

386
00:23:28,574 --> 00:23:31,644
This curtain opens electronically.

387
00:23:32,211 --> 00:23:36,382
Please take a look at the gorgeous
European garden out there.

388
00:23:36,983 --> 00:23:40,720
The cost included periodic care
by the gardener.

389
00:23:44,056 --> 00:23:44,991
Your fly is open.

390
00:23:46,526 --> 00:23:49,996
Oh? Excuse me!

391
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:56,502
Prince Adachi is a bit off lately.

392
00:23:56,669 --> 00:23:59,705
I can't believe his fly was open!

393
00:23:59,872 --> 00:24:01,140
Let's go home.

394
00:24:04,343 --> 00:24:05,812
SOUTH HAMAMATSU, NIWANO

395
00:24:05,978 --> 00:24:08,147
The course is straight
from the fourth corner.

396
00:24:08,314 --> 00:24:10,950
Kimiha Gold is in the lead.

397
00:24:11,117 --> 00:24:12,652
Oh, Seiji, what's going on?

398
00:24:13,653 --> 00:24:17,356
For someone who's chasing his dream,
you seem lazy.

399
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:22,495
I was just watching the news.
We need to know what's going on.

400
00:24:23,429 --> 00:24:24,664
Whatever.

401
00:24:25,064 --> 00:24:27,967
It's too much to prepare tea.
Do you want to go out for eel?

402
00:24:28,134 --> 00:24:29,468
I won't sell this house.

403
00:24:30,203 --> 00:24:33,406
What? You came all the way
to Hamamatsu to tell me that?

404
00:24:33,573 --> 00:24:34,841
Right.

405
00:24:35,374 --> 00:24:38,344
Let's talk about that over an eel--

406
00:24:38,511 --> 00:24:43,082
I don't have time.
I only took the morning off.

407
00:24:43,549 --> 00:24:47,954
I will not sign off on it,
so just live on what I send you.

408
00:24:50,489 --> 00:24:56,429
I was a horrible father to you
and a horrible husband to your mother.

409
00:24:59,832 --> 00:25:06,372
That's why I want to repay you
and make up to you! Please!

410
00:25:06,706 --> 00:25:07,740
Stop that.

411
00:25:07,907 --> 00:25:12,578
Please, give me this last chance!
If the takoyaki shop is a success,

412
00:25:12,979 --> 00:25:14,780
I can die!

413
00:25:15,381 --> 00:25:20,186
Seiji, please! Please let my dream
come true! Please, Seiji!

414
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:23,189
Please!

415
00:25:29,862 --> 00:25:30,863
You know,

416
00:25:31,397 --> 00:25:37,403
Ms. Sangenya actually found
a buyer for me.

417
00:25:38,337 --> 00:25:42,408
That person came here last night.

418
00:25:42,575 --> 00:25:45,411
His name was Mr. Rusudo.

419
00:25:45,578 --> 00:25:48,281
He said he knows you.

420
00:25:48,581 --> 00:25:51,784
This deal is going forward.

421
00:25:51,951 --> 00:25:54,487
No matter how much you are against it,

422
00:25:54,654 --> 00:25:59,525
the fate of this house is moving
towards being sold.

423
00:26:02,962 --> 00:26:06,666
Oh Seiji, do you understand it now?

424
00:26:08,100 --> 00:26:10,303
Thank you.

425
00:26:10,469 --> 00:26:13,973
Why does Chief Sangenya
always drive me into a corner?

426
00:26:16,008 --> 00:26:17,743
She even collaborated with Mr. Rusudo.

427
00:26:21,647 --> 00:26:22,815
Hello.

428
00:26:22,982 --> 00:26:24,083
Chief Sangenya.

429
00:26:24,617 --> 00:26:28,287
Ms. Sangenya, my son finally understands.

430
00:26:28,454 --> 00:26:29,689
Is that so?

431
00:26:30,022 --> 00:26:34,026
I don't understand why you,
whom I respect so much,

432
00:26:34,193 --> 00:26:36,228
are doing such an unjust thing.

433
00:26:36,395 --> 00:26:39,165
You've been selling houses
for your clients' happiness.

434
00:26:39,865 --> 00:26:41,534
No one will be happy this way.

435
00:26:41,701 --> 00:26:45,705
Stop whining, just leave everything
to me and get back to work!

436
00:26:45,871 --> 00:26:47,206
I'm… I'm…

437
00:26:47,373 --> 00:26:49,308
Go immediately. Go!

438
00:26:51,944 --> 00:26:52,845
Yes.

439
00:26:59,318 --> 00:27:01,120
That was your "Go".

440
00:27:02,221 --> 00:27:04,190
Could you do it again?

441
00:27:04,357 --> 00:27:05,992
-I will not.
-Yes ma'am.

442
00:27:09,128 --> 00:27:10,563
This is Sangenya.

443
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:13,466
Oh, you answered. Sangenjaya?

444
00:27:13,799 --> 00:27:16,736
I have an interesting story,
you interested?

445
00:27:17,837 --> 00:27:23,342
Don't hang up! Don't hang up!
I'll tell you something big!

446
00:27:25,277 --> 00:27:29,315
Manager Yashiro is cheating on you.

447
00:27:32,184 --> 00:27:36,889
I got an outrageous tip.

448
00:27:37,056 --> 00:27:39,825
Excuse me, it's an inconvenience
to the other customers.

449
00:27:39,992 --> 00:27:41,127
Please make your calls outside.

450
00:27:41,293 --> 00:27:42,962
Shut up! I'll hang up now.

451
00:27:43,462 --> 00:27:45,798
In any case, just come
to the cafe in Harajuku.

452
00:27:45,965 --> 00:27:49,435
If you don't come, you'll regret
it for the rest of your life.

453
00:27:53,706 --> 00:27:55,307
Is something the matter?

454
00:27:56,142 --> 00:27:57,443
It's nothing.

455
00:27:58,544 --> 00:27:59,879
Here you go.

456
00:28:00,046 --> 00:28:02,615
What's taking her so long,
that Sangenjaya!

457
00:28:03,182 --> 00:28:05,918
I've been waiting for two hours now.

458
00:28:10,222 --> 00:28:13,526
I won't be shocked
with your sudden appearance.

459
00:28:15,528 --> 00:28:18,397
Say something like,
"There is no property I can't sell"

460
00:28:18,564 --> 00:28:21,033
or "It's my job to sell properties".

461
00:28:22,768 --> 00:28:24,670
You won't say anything?

462
00:28:24,837 --> 00:28:26,072
Have you decided?

463
00:28:26,238 --> 00:28:30,176
This pancake is delicious. It's fluffy.

464
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:32,344
I'll have another

465
00:28:32,511 --> 00:28:35,548
banana chocolate pancake
with whipped cream and maple syrup,

466
00:28:35,714 --> 00:28:37,983
with a double scoop of ice cream
and fruits.

467
00:28:38,150 --> 00:28:39,452
Oh, and a hot cafe au lait.

468
00:28:39,618 --> 00:28:41,053
Certainly.

469
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,788
It's your treat.

470
00:28:44,657 --> 00:28:47,126
It's the price of your husband's secret.

471
00:28:47,293 --> 00:28:50,729
Husband's secret, Yabatanien.

472
00:28:51,864 --> 00:28:53,499
Really Manji.

473
00:28:54,533 --> 00:28:57,803
You've become a little crazy.

474
00:28:57,970 --> 00:29:04,243
So even you get rattled, huh?
Then let me rattle you more! Here!

475
00:29:08,114 --> 00:29:13,085
Things between those two
have already begun.

476
00:29:13,853 --> 00:29:16,989
That tall woman Manager is embracing,

477
00:29:17,156 --> 00:29:19,992
has eyes like this,
when she's looking at men.

478
00:29:23,462 --> 00:29:26,866
Manager is so naive,
he immediately fell for it!

479
00:29:27,233 --> 00:29:29,835
What is on the floor here?

480
00:29:30,269 --> 00:29:32,471
They're cans of mackerel, mustard flavor.

481
00:29:35,574 --> 00:29:37,710
-Wait one second.
-Is there more?

482
00:29:38,611 --> 00:29:40,846
Don't underestimate the Mika cannon.

483
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:44,250
I have more!

484
00:29:45,017 --> 00:29:48,521
It's not just the cans of mackerel!

485
00:29:52,424 --> 00:29:56,695
I won't tell you what happened
after this, but if you insist,

486
00:29:56,862 --> 00:29:59,832
I may tell you. In exchange for--

487
00:30:01,967 --> 00:30:03,068
She disappeared out of shock.

488
00:30:03,903 --> 00:30:07,439
Oh wait! She took my smartphone too!
Move out of the way!

489
00:30:19,251 --> 00:30:20,920
She was on fire!

490
00:30:34,934 --> 00:30:36,402
Sangenya? What's the matter?

491
00:30:38,671 --> 00:30:40,272
What are you rushing for?

492
00:30:40,940 --> 00:30:42,641
-Niwano!
-Yes!

493
00:30:43,509 --> 00:30:46,111
Your voice is too soft.
Your tie is crooked.

494
00:30:46,278 --> 00:30:48,547
That style of suit is horrible! Answer!

495
00:30:49,014 --> 00:30:53,352
Niwano, what are you good at
besides answering energetically?

496
00:30:55,754 --> 00:30:58,157
Niwano, what is your job?

497
00:30:58,490 --> 00:31:01,594
-It's to sell properties.
-I can't hear you.

498
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:03,495
-It's to sell properties.
-I can't hear you.

499
00:31:03,662 --> 00:31:04,496
It's to sell propert--

500
00:31:04,663 --> 00:31:07,466
-Okay, it's time. Let's go!
-Yes!

501
00:31:10,903 --> 00:31:12,871
-Manager.
-Yes?

502
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:14,206
I'm going to work.

503
00:31:14,373 --> 00:31:15,474
Good luck.

504
00:31:17,710 --> 00:31:21,714
My job is to sell properties.

505
00:31:27,152 --> 00:31:28,254
What did you say?

506
00:31:28,821 --> 00:31:30,556
Thank you for being concerned for me…

507
00:31:31,423 --> 00:31:36,161
but I decided to let my mother's
dreams come true.

508
00:31:36,562 --> 00:31:37,830
Oh…

509
00:31:38,364 --> 00:31:41,834
She said, "Please, please believe in me."

510
00:31:42,001 --> 00:31:44,570
She said it several hundred times.
I got brainwashed.

511
00:31:46,472 --> 00:31:50,976
Thank you very much. As for the property
you'll purchase after you sell your house,

512
00:31:51,443 --> 00:31:54,146
I could give you a tour of it,
if you like.

513
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:55,981
Please.

514
00:31:58,550 --> 00:32:00,219
This is a cute house. When I was younger,

515
00:32:00,386 --> 00:32:04,757
I always wanted to live
in a place like this.

516
00:32:05,124 --> 00:32:07,593
But this won't do to meet my needs now.
It's too small.

517
00:32:08,093 --> 00:32:11,130
How do I run a cake shop here?

518
00:32:11,297 --> 00:32:16,302
I want a place where that can be used both
as a shop and a school to teach classes.

519
00:32:16,468 --> 00:32:20,673
Ms. Sachiko. This is a house
in which you'll live alone.

520
00:32:21,507 --> 00:32:22,574
What?

521
00:32:23,175 --> 00:32:24,109
Ms. Sumire.

522
00:32:24,910 --> 00:32:25,778
Yes?

523
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:27,713
This is your only life.

524
00:32:33,519 --> 00:32:36,555
You don't have to be your mother's v…

525
00:32:47,566 --> 00:32:49,101
What's the matter?

526
00:32:52,371 --> 00:32:56,442
Your voice is gone? Oh no!
I'll call an ambulance.

527
00:32:56,875 --> 00:32:57,743
NIWANO!

528
00:33:00,779 --> 00:33:02,114
TRANSLATE

529
00:33:02,281 --> 00:33:03,682
Tra… Tra…

530
00:33:03,849 --> 00:33:06,418
TRA…

531
00:33:06,585 --> 00:33:11,256
Translate? I got it.

532
00:33:13,359 --> 00:33:15,060
YOU SHOULDN'T BE YOUR MOTHER'S VICTIM

533
00:33:15,227 --> 00:33:18,030
Your mother's v…

534
00:33:18,197 --> 00:33:20,399
YOU SHOULDN'T BE YOUR MOTHER'S VICTIM

535
00:33:21,266 --> 00:33:22,267
I got it.

536
00:33:23,302 --> 00:33:25,971
You shouldn't be your mother's victim.

537
00:33:26,372 --> 00:33:31,043
I didn't tell her to be my victim.
I'm asking her to dream with me.

538
00:33:33,645 --> 00:33:34,813
PLEASE

539
00:33:34,980 --> 00:33:38,117
Please…

540
00:33:39,184 --> 00:33:40,953
don't drag your daughter

541
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:43,789
into your own dream.

542
00:33:44,223 --> 00:33:46,825
That's right. I think so too.

543
00:33:52,331 --> 00:33:55,501
Ms. Sachiko's life

544
00:33:56,168 --> 00:33:59,571
is Ms. Sachiko's life.

545
00:33:59,738 --> 00:34:02,107
Ms. Sumire's life

546
00:34:02,274 --> 00:34:05,444
is Ms. Sumire's life.

547
00:34:05,978 --> 00:34:08,280
That's so true. That's right.

548
00:34:08,447 --> 00:34:10,482
No need for you to go
along with your mother's dream.

549
00:34:10,649 --> 00:34:12,551
I'm in the same situation as you,
Ms. Sumire.

550
00:34:12,985 --> 00:34:16,121
It's hard for us to push them away
when it's just you and the parent.

551
00:34:16,288 --> 00:34:18,357
But I think that's not it.

552
00:34:20,726 --> 00:34:25,397
Oh, I'm sorry, I said more
than what she said.

553
00:34:29,234 --> 00:34:30,302
It's fine?

554
00:34:31,570 --> 00:34:34,339
You talk now.

555
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:37,476
What? Niwano is going to talk?
I can't do it.

556
00:34:37,643 --> 00:34:38,811
NIWANO, GO!

557
00:34:39,278 --> 00:34:40,379
Yes!

558
00:34:47,252 --> 00:34:52,124
Ms. Sumire, I'm in the same
situation as you, and I think

559
00:34:53,292 --> 00:34:57,296
you've had enough of being
dragged around by your parent.

560
00:34:58,163 --> 00:34:59,264
Yes.

561
00:34:59,932 --> 00:35:01,333
Sumire!

562
00:35:01,500 --> 00:35:05,737
Then, you need to protect yourself.

563
00:35:05,904 --> 00:35:08,040
Otherwise, your mother
will take everything from you!

564
00:35:08,207 --> 00:35:10,008
-What are you saying?
-Society considers…

565
00:35:11,009 --> 00:35:12,878
being devoted to our parents
as a good deed.

566
00:35:13,378 --> 00:35:15,547
I was bound by that too.

567
00:35:15,881 --> 00:35:18,417
But when you mature
and become independent,

568
00:35:18,584 --> 00:35:23,088
a parent's life is their life
and a child's life is their life!

569
00:35:23,388 --> 00:35:26,959
It's fine if we think differently.
If what you want to do about

570
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:32,264
the house is different,
then sell your house, divide the assets,

571
00:35:32,431 --> 00:35:35,367
then you both do whatever you want to do.

572
00:35:35,534 --> 00:35:37,803
That's it! That is it!

573
00:35:37,970 --> 00:35:38,971
NIWANO, GO!

574
00:35:39,137 --> 00:35:40,005
Yes!

575
00:35:40,873 --> 00:35:43,075
There is no need to be
bound by your parents.

576
00:35:43,242 --> 00:35:44,710
Cut your relations with her now!

577
00:35:44,877 --> 00:35:49,147
Stop clinging on to your daughter!
Release that bond!

578
00:35:49,314 --> 00:35:53,452
Who cares about being
devoted to your parent?

579
00:36:02,995 --> 00:36:05,564
I'm sorry. I said too much.

580
00:36:09,868 --> 00:36:10,903
I got it.

581
00:36:12,371 --> 00:36:13,672
I'll sell that house…

582
00:36:14,706 --> 00:36:20,212
and I'll buy a studio
with my half of the asset.

583
00:36:21,346 --> 00:36:22,281
I'll live by myself.

584
00:36:23,815 --> 00:36:25,050
Sumire!

585
00:36:26,318 --> 00:36:28,253
That was my dream all this time,

586
00:36:29,254 --> 00:36:33,292
but I thought I shouldn't say such
a thing and suppressed myself.

587
00:36:35,260 --> 00:36:37,429
Mr. Niwano, thank you very much.

588
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:41,934
Sumire, I'm going to be alone.

589
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:43,135
Mom…

590
00:36:44,870 --> 00:36:49,341
Please let go of the idea
that a child belongs to their parents.

591
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:56,014
Yes.

592
00:37:01,753 --> 00:37:04,523
Mrs. Sachiko Munakata
and Ms. Sumire Munakata,

593
00:37:05,791 --> 00:37:08,961
your home will be sold for
¥50 million by Teiko Real Estate.

594
00:37:09,828 --> 00:37:13,332
And Ms. Sachiko, this home is ¥10 million.

595
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:16,735
I'll sell my portion.

596
00:37:19,204 --> 00:37:20,906
What about my cake shop?

597
00:37:21,073 --> 00:37:22,908
You can do it if you want to.

598
00:37:24,209 --> 00:37:26,912
I'll sell that home for ¥50 million.

599
00:37:33,919 --> 00:37:35,354
Thank you very much.

600
00:37:37,656 --> 00:37:38,724
We got them.

601
00:37:39,424 --> 00:37:40,993
ON-SITE SALE
OPEN HOUSE

602
00:37:42,694 --> 00:37:45,998
This curtain opens electronically.

603
00:37:46,765 --> 00:37:51,470
Please take a look at that gorgeous
European garden out there.

604
00:37:52,504 --> 00:37:56,375
The cost includes
the gardening fee as well.

605
00:37:57,075 --> 00:37:58,877
This is wonderful.

606
00:37:59,044 --> 00:38:04,349
Madam, the moment you find your house
is like when you fall in love.

607
00:38:05,183 --> 00:38:09,321
Please be careful not to let go
of a fateful encounter.

608
00:38:10,055 --> 00:38:13,759
This house is far from the station.
It's scary at night.

609
00:38:13,925 --> 00:38:15,427
Please, do not worry.

610
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:21,466
This area is bright
since many houses are illuminated.

611
00:38:21,633 --> 00:38:25,237
And you will be able to enjoy
a different ambience at night.

612
00:38:26,571 --> 00:38:27,606
Wonderful.

613
00:38:28,106 --> 00:38:32,678
This house has different charms
during the day and at night.

614
00:38:32,944 --> 00:38:35,814
It's just like me.

615
00:38:36,581 --> 00:38:39,317
Prince Adachi at night?

616
00:38:39,484 --> 00:38:43,321
Madam, this property is very popular,

617
00:38:43,488 --> 00:38:46,892
so unless you apply fast,
it will be off the market soon.

618
00:38:47,059 --> 00:38:48,493
I'll buy it! I'll buy!

619
00:38:49,394 --> 00:38:50,829
Thank you very much.

620
00:38:53,031 --> 00:38:54,800
Manager!

621
00:38:55,333 --> 00:38:59,404
It's terrible! Chief Sangenya lost
her voice all of a sudden.

622
00:38:59,571 --> 00:39:00,505
What?

623
00:39:00,672 --> 00:39:02,240
I told her to go to a hospital.

624
00:39:13,752 --> 00:39:18,223
Manager, Munakata family's house
was sold for ¥50 million by Niwano.

625
00:39:18,790 --> 00:39:21,193
It wasn't me, but Niwano sold it.

626
00:39:22,594 --> 00:39:24,563
-She has her voice.
-Oh?

627
00:39:24,730 --> 00:39:26,465
What? Niwano sold a house?

628
00:39:27,065 --> 00:39:29,568
-That's because her voice--
-Yes, he did.

629
00:39:30,335 --> 00:39:33,138
It wasn't me, but Niwano sold it.

630
00:39:39,111 --> 00:39:41,580
Yes, I sold it.

631
00:39:42,214 --> 00:39:44,850
Oh, Niwano, good job.

632
00:39:45,016 --> 00:39:46,818
Way to go! Niwano!

633
00:39:47,853 --> 00:39:49,921
Yeah! Niwano!

634
00:39:50,489 --> 00:39:52,357
Adachi, welcome back.

635
00:39:54,259 --> 00:39:55,560
Congratulations, Niwano.

636
00:39:55,727 --> 00:39:57,129
Thank you very much.

637
00:39:58,230 --> 00:40:02,000
Manager, the house in
Nishifujimidai sold for ¥80 million.

638
00:40:02,634 --> 00:40:05,170
Adachi! Good job!

639
00:40:06,938 --> 00:40:08,473
I'm the Chief!

640
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:11,676
-That's right.
-Prince Adachi is back!

641
00:40:11,843 --> 00:40:13,678
Way to go! Adachi!

642
00:40:14,412 --> 00:40:15,714
Prince Adachi!

643
00:40:15,881 --> 00:40:17,349
-Prince Adachi!
-Adachi!

644
00:40:18,150 --> 00:40:19,918
NIWANO

645
00:40:20,085 --> 00:40:21,953
CONTRACT

646
00:40:23,455 --> 00:40:26,158
We'll sell this house,
but I'll take my portion.

647
00:40:27,526 --> 00:40:30,695
Then I won't be able
to do a takoyaki shop.

648
00:40:30,862 --> 00:40:33,064
I don't care about that.

649
00:40:33,231 --> 00:40:38,170
What's up with you?
Why are you being so cold?

650
00:40:39,037 --> 00:40:41,573
Then I'll cut my ties with you.

651
00:40:42,073 --> 00:40:43,341
That's fine, go ahead.

652
00:40:43,508 --> 00:40:47,412
What? You don't sound like yourself.

653
00:40:48,246 --> 00:40:51,683
-I've been released.
-Huh?

654
00:40:52,884 --> 00:40:54,119
I've been released.

655
00:40:58,223 --> 00:41:01,459
Sign this and send it to
Teiko Real Estate's Shinjuku office.

656
00:41:01,626 --> 00:41:04,796
I have to catch my bullet train. See you!

657
00:41:08,366 --> 00:41:12,938
He's so cold now.

658
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:18,910
Oh? Did he change his mind?

659
00:41:24,316 --> 00:41:27,052
I brought the deposit for this home.

660
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:32,891
My son said that he'll take half
of what this house sells for.

661
00:41:34,125 --> 00:41:36,661
Now my dream is over.

662
00:41:39,764 --> 00:41:41,366
That's not true.

663
00:41:42,067 --> 00:41:47,038
I will help you, Mr. Shigeo Niwano,
in making your dream come true.

664
00:41:51,009 --> 00:41:52,544
Winner, Adachi.

665
00:42:00,218 --> 00:42:01,119
You are on.

666
00:42:05,056 --> 00:42:06,124
Kenji.

667
00:42:08,059 --> 00:42:10,428
I found the answer.

668
00:42:12,731 --> 00:42:16,134
There was nothing I wanted to do.

669
00:42:17,168 --> 00:42:18,503
I realized that.

670
00:42:19,304 --> 00:42:20,171
I see.

671
00:42:21,139 --> 00:42:23,875
But I still like you, Kenji.

672
00:42:24,876 --> 00:42:27,312
I like you too, Satoshi.

673
00:42:29,814 --> 00:42:30,649
Thank you.

674
00:42:31,483 --> 00:42:32,584
Do you want to get a drink?

675
00:42:33,518 --> 00:42:35,553
I don't think I'll go today.

676
00:42:35,987 --> 00:42:37,188
Some other time.

677
00:42:44,663 --> 00:42:47,165
Today, it's Niwano self-special.

678
00:42:47,332 --> 00:42:49,601
What is this "self-special"?

679
00:42:49,768 --> 00:42:51,569
Prince Adachi, you look refreshed.

680
00:42:52,137 --> 00:42:53,672
I guess it's because I graduated.

681
00:42:54,839 --> 00:42:57,008
Niwano, it seems that you graduated
from Sanchi.

682
00:42:57,175 --> 00:42:59,778
-Really?
-I wonder if I did.

683
00:42:59,945 --> 00:43:01,212
What? You don't sound confident.

684
00:43:01,813 --> 00:43:04,015
Oh, by the way, Mr. Adachi,
who did you graduate from?

685
00:43:05,583 --> 00:43:08,954
I graduated from Kenji Rusudo.

686
00:43:11,089 --> 00:43:13,191
What? What does that mean?

687
00:43:13,358 --> 00:43:14,926
That's not important.

688
00:43:15,093 --> 00:43:17,963
I'm happy for you. Congrats for
graduating, Prince Adachi.

689
00:43:18,129 --> 00:43:18,997
Thank you.

690
00:43:19,931 --> 00:43:21,433
I graduated from my dad.

691
00:43:21,599 --> 00:43:23,368
Congratulations, Niwano.

692
00:43:23,535 --> 00:43:29,407
Why don't you graduate from Sanchi too?
Then you'll see it's nothing.

693
00:43:30,709 --> 00:43:35,714
So today, Chief Sangenya lost
her voice in front of our clients.

694
00:43:35,981 --> 00:43:39,551
It came back, but I wonder
if she really lost her voice.

695
00:43:39,718 --> 00:43:40,885
What do you mean?

696
00:43:41,386 --> 00:43:45,223
I just had a thought that maybe
she was trying to get me to graduate.

697
00:43:45,390 --> 00:43:47,492
You didn't graduate if you think that.

698
00:43:47,659 --> 00:43:48,493
I know.

699
00:43:48,927 --> 00:43:52,697
But I've heard that you lose
your voice because of stress.

700
00:43:53,198 --> 00:43:55,867
It's called aphonia.
I saw it on TV the other day.

701
00:43:56,034 --> 00:43:58,003
Would Sanchi stress about something?

702
00:43:59,504 --> 00:44:02,307
Well, Yashiro has a lot going on lately…

703
00:44:02,474 --> 00:44:05,043
-What do you mean?
-What happened to Manager?

704
00:44:06,011 --> 00:44:09,114
It's nothing.
Let's toast to celebrate graduation.

705
00:44:09,781 --> 00:44:13,785
-Alrighty!
-Cheers!

706
00:44:14,319 --> 00:44:16,821
Youthful times

707
00:44:17,422 --> 00:44:20,658
Is a dream

708
00:44:20,825 --> 00:44:22,460
Later…

709
00:44:22,627 --> 00:44:26,197
Whether Chief Sangenya had aphonia or not,

710
00:44:26,364 --> 00:44:28,600
is something I will never know.

711
00:44:29,300 --> 00:44:34,105
And I will never know
how I truly feel either.

712
00:44:34,272 --> 00:44:39,511
All you do is hesitate

713
00:44:40,245 --> 00:44:44,349
I'm sorry, apple pie is sold out.

714
00:44:44,516 --> 00:44:45,550
That's a pity.

715
00:44:46,384 --> 00:44:48,653
I love the apple pie here.

716
00:44:48,820 --> 00:44:51,623
It's powdery like the one
my mom used to make.

717
00:44:51,790 --> 00:44:55,927
Oh really? Then do you want
to be my son? I'm kidding!

718
00:44:56,961 --> 00:44:58,329
Shige!

719
00:44:58,496 --> 00:45:02,333
Putting eel in takoyaki is a nice idea.

720
00:45:02,500 --> 00:45:06,204
Right? This is Rusudo's idea.

721
00:45:06,371 --> 00:45:10,442
Rusudo got this food stand
for a reasonable price too.

722
00:45:10,608 --> 00:45:13,878
I like Rusudo. He's very handsome.

723
00:45:14,045 --> 00:45:17,882
-What? You have me and yet--
-Excuse me!

724
00:45:18,049 --> 00:45:18,950
Welcome, welcome.

725
00:45:26,357 --> 00:45:28,560
Can't you do the rest tomorrow?

726
00:45:29,027 --> 00:45:29,928
I can.

727
00:45:30,395 --> 00:45:31,496
Let's go home then.

728
00:45:35,166 --> 00:45:36,801
What's the matter?

729
00:45:37,235 --> 00:45:39,003
Please stop having an affair.

730
00:45:39,604 --> 00:45:40,438
An affair?

731
00:45:40,605 --> 00:45:41,606
Yes.

732
00:45:41,940 --> 00:45:44,476
I wouldn't do such a thing.

733
00:45:45,076 --> 00:45:47,445
Then what is this?

734
00:45:48,346 --> 00:45:49,547
Where did you get this?

735
00:45:50,014 --> 00:45:53,651
Mika Shirasu said that things between
the two of you have already started.

736
00:45:56,488 --> 00:46:02,994
This is when Shirasu piled up cans
of mackerel so high,

737
00:46:03,161 --> 00:46:07,031
and all those cans came crashing down,

738
00:46:07,198 --> 00:46:10,568
and this person happened to be under it,
so I protected her.

739
00:46:11,436 --> 00:46:12,937
Did you protect her because it was her?

740
00:46:13,271 --> 00:46:15,440
I think I would have protected
Shirasu too.

741
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:17,308
She is very sexy…

742
00:46:19,511 --> 00:46:21,746
and looks at you like that.

743
00:46:22,046 --> 00:46:23,982
I don't know that.

744
00:46:24,149 --> 00:46:28,653
Isn't it strange that you believe
in Mika Shirasu, and not me?

745
00:46:28,820 --> 00:46:30,755
You don't trust me, Sangenya?

746
00:46:31,122 --> 00:46:32,924
I trusted you until this morning.

747
00:46:33,825 --> 00:46:36,628
I just protected her here.

748
00:46:36,794 --> 00:46:37,662
You two are embracing.

749
00:46:37,829 --> 00:46:40,798
It just looks that way in the photo.

750
00:46:40,965 --> 00:46:47,438
I did this, and I went like this,
so that is why it looks that way.

751
00:46:47,605 --> 00:46:49,541
How many times do I have to tell you
to get it?

752
00:46:49,707 --> 00:46:52,177
Then what is this?

753
00:46:53,811 --> 00:46:56,981
You two are holding hands
and are about to go into a hotel.

754
00:46:58,583 --> 00:46:59,484
I didn't go in.

755
00:47:00,652 --> 00:47:06,357
I didn't go in. On that day,
she asked me to go eat oden,

756
00:47:06,658 --> 00:47:10,161
and I figured you would be coming
home really late,

757
00:47:10,328 --> 00:47:13,464
so I figured eating oden would be fine.
I'll admit that.

758
00:47:13,831 --> 00:47:17,769
She told me her friend's oden shop
was close by,

759
00:47:17,936 --> 00:47:19,504
so I trusted her and went,

760
00:47:19,804 --> 00:47:22,607
then we were surrounded
by hotels all of a sudden.

761
00:47:22,774 --> 00:47:26,778
When I was all "huh?", she was like,
"Let's go in here!"

762
00:47:26,945 --> 00:47:28,746
Soon as I said, "No",

763
00:47:28,913 --> 00:47:32,350
and fortunately the hotel's "no vacancy"
light came on.

764
00:47:32,517 --> 00:47:38,289
Then she pulled me next door,
but I said no and resisted.

765
00:47:38,456 --> 00:47:42,360
Then she slapped my face really hard.

766
00:47:43,461 --> 00:47:44,562
Slapped in the face?

767
00:47:45,496 --> 00:47:48,233
In other words, what I want to say is…

768
00:47:51,469 --> 00:47:54,772
please trust me. I did not have an affair.

769
00:47:58,176 --> 00:47:59,010
Do you get it?

770
00:48:01,546 --> 00:48:02,614
Do you believe me now?

771
00:48:07,085 --> 00:48:10,922
If you don't believe me,
then I have something to say too.

772
00:48:11,689 --> 00:48:14,192
Why were you secretly meeting

773
00:48:14,359 --> 00:48:19,063
with that Rusudo guy? You met with
him at that elementary school.

774
00:48:19,497 --> 00:48:23,334
I just went to ask why Yoshio Sanpei
was following me.

775
00:48:23,501 --> 00:48:25,803
We didn't hold each other
or go to a hotel!

776
00:48:25,970 --> 00:48:29,474
But he told you he loves you.

777
00:48:29,641 --> 00:48:32,577
You called him "Yoshio-chan"
and he called you "Manchichi".

778
00:48:32,744 --> 00:48:35,213
Even if Yoshio Sanpei loves me,

779
00:48:35,747 --> 00:48:37,582
I only love Manager.

780
00:48:41,886 --> 00:48:42,854
But

781
00:48:43,554 --> 00:48:46,124
I can't do anything
about how the other one feels.

782
00:48:48,693 --> 00:48:50,028
And her feelings too.

783
00:48:52,797 --> 00:48:58,536
So let's leave the other one's
feelings for now

784
00:49:00,838 --> 00:49:05,176
and let's trust each other.

785
00:49:07,879 --> 00:49:10,448
-We are supposedly married.
-Supposedly?

786
00:49:10,615 --> 00:49:12,450
I'll take back "supposedly".

787
00:49:13,451 --> 00:49:16,020
We are married.

788
00:49:18,189 --> 00:49:22,827
I got it. I will trust you, Manager.

789
00:49:23,695 --> 00:49:26,764
I will trust you too, Sangenya.

790
00:49:31,836 --> 00:49:34,939
Now, shall we go home together?

791
00:49:36,441 --> 00:49:37,342
Yes.

792
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:43,514
Manager.

793
00:49:45,383 --> 00:49:46,918
I want to hold hands.

794
00:50:36,434 --> 00:50:38,202
Playing friendship won't sell a house!

795
00:50:38,369 --> 00:50:40,338
-Thanks for working hard.
-It's my first job.

796
00:50:40,505 --> 00:50:41,439
Niwano!

797
00:50:41,606 --> 00:50:45,009
A house is a home when someone
lives in it. Figure that out.

798
00:50:45,176 --> 00:50:47,612
-You've mistaken me for someone else.
-That's not true!

799
00:50:47,779 --> 00:50:50,848
I won't forgive Machi Sangenya.
